  m_Name: Lumbar_Vertebrae_L1_L3
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Lumbar_Vertebrae_L1_L3
  partName: Lumbar Vertebrae L1 L3
  descriptionChunks:
  - The lumbar vertebrae L1 through L3 form the cranial portion of the canine lower
    back and contribute significantly to spinal flexibility and support. These vertebrae
    bear substantial body weight while protecting the spinal cord and associated
    nerves. Their large vertebral bodies and processes provide attachment sites
  - for powerful trunk and hindlimb muscles involved in posture and locomotion. The
    lumbar region allows controlled bending and extension during movement while maintaining
    spinal stability. Proper alignment and muscular support are essential for efficient
    transmission of forces between the trunk and hindlimbs.
